**Question of the day: Why do computers need three types of memory?**  
Short answer: the same reason humans do\!

*  Short term memory  
*  Long term memory  
* SUPER short term momory (stream of thoughts)

# **Human Example: Hangman**

Let’s demonstrate how humans use their three types of memory by playing hangman together.

**What is the name of half of a byte?**

| N\_ | i\_ | b\_ | b\_ | l\_ | e\_ |
| :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |

| LONG-TERM MEMORYWhat you must remember in order to play Hangman at all | SHORT-TERM MEMORYWhat you must remember only until the current puzzle is finished.   | VERY SHORT-TERM MEMORYWhat you must remember for just a brief moment while solving the current puzzle |
| ----- | :---- | :---- |
| Rules of hangman The english alphabet  | Letters you guessed which are correct/incorrect The status of your hangman | Remembering the letter you are currently guessing |
| This is like **secondary storage.** | This is like **RAM** | This is like **registers.** |

**Comparing the 3 types of memory**

|  | Secondary storage ![][image1]![][image2] | RAM ![][image3] | Registers (inside CPU) ![][image4] |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| **Storage Size** | Largest (TB of data) | Medium (dozens fo GB) | Small (Bits) |
| **Duration** | Permanent (Until device breaks) | Until the application being used is closed | VERY Short (nanoseconds) |
| **Speed** | By comparison of the other 2 items, slow | Pretty fast | SUPER fast |
| **Where it is** | Varies (External or internal) | Internal plugged into the motherboard | Inside the CPU |
| **Price per GB (per storage)** | **Cheapest** | Meduim, cheaper then secondary (currently due to AI ddr5 more expensive) | Every expensive (we can’t buy separate from CPU) |
